00:04:17,800 --> 00:04:19,800
Standups and Kanban.

106
00:04:20,620 --> 00:04:22,620
So, what is a standup? 

107
00:04:22,820 --> 00:04:24,820
In many American sports such -

108
00:04:24,840 --> 00:04:26,400
as football and rugby,

109
00:04:26,470 --> 00:04:28,890
the team has a huddle before each play. 

110
00:04:29,090 --> 00:04:31,090
The huddle is short and strategic.

111
00:04:31,160 --> 00:04:33,030
It keeps the team informed,

112
00:04:33,090 --> 00:04:33,900
connected,

113
00:04:33,930 --> 00:04:35,930
and calibrated throughout the game. 

114
00:04:36,140 --> 00:04:37,910
For software teams,

115
00:04:38,070 --> 00:04:40,210
the standup is much like a team's huddle,

116
00:04:40,250 --> 00:04:43,730
and we usually refer to this as a "scrum meeting".

117
00:04:43,930 --> 00:04:45,580
In other words, 

118
00:04:45,630 --> 00:04:47,630
scrums are a daily meeting that -

119
00:04:47,670 --> 00:04:49,670
involves the core team; such as your -

120
00:04:49,690 --> 00:04:50,780
project managers,

121
00:04:50,790 --> 00:04:52,790
your clients, and developers.

122
00:04:53,570 --> 00:04:54,710
For your group project,

123
00:04:54,910 --> 00:04:57,940
 this will just be all the team members. 

124
00:04:58,140 --> 00:05:00,140
Although standups can vary -

125
00:05:00,280 --> 00:05:02,360
across different teams and corporations,

126
00:05:02,480 --> 00:05:05,170
we usually have 3 very simple questions -

127
00:05:05,230 --> 00:05:08,320
that each person takes in turns to answer. 

128
00:05:09,540 --> 00:05:13,720
1. What work have I completed since the last standup? 

129
00:05:13,920 --> 00:05:18,780
2. What new tasks can I work on until the next standup? 

130
00:05:18,950 --> 00:05:23,610
and 3. What issues came across that are blocking my progress? 

131
00:05:24,620 --> 00:05:27,560
Standups are supposed to be kept short and efficient, 

132
00:05:27,580 --> 00:05:29,490
so each person usually spends -

133
00:05:29,520 --> 00:05:31,520
no more than a couple minutes talking.

134
00:05:31,740 --> 00:05:32,790
Hence a standup,

135
00:05:32,850 --> 00:05:34,850
you stand up and give a short talk.

136
00:05:35,100 --> 00:05:37,680
It's also strongly recommended -

137
00:05:37,710 --> 00:05:39,710
that you have someone on rotation -

138
00:05:39,750 --> 00:05:41,830
every standup to write your meeting minute,

139
00:05:41,880 --> 00:05:45,300
so you don't have to "remember" or "make them up" later.

140
