144
00:05:54,880 --> 00:05:58,050
within the context of Agile work methodology.

145
00:05:58,800 --> 00:06:00,870
Kanban, is actually a Japanese term -

146
00:06:00,950 --> 00:06:01,980
for billboard.

147
00:06:02,150 --> 00:06:04,150
And in the context of Agile,

148
00:06:04,410 --> 00:06:06,410
Kanban boards have tasks that are - 

149
00:06:06,430 --> 00:06:09,560
represented visually as a card on the board,

150
00:06:09,580 --> 00:06:11,580
allowing all team members to see the -

151
00:06:11,630 --> 00:06:14,550
progress of each task at any time.

152
00:06:14,750 --> 00:06:16,750
Now, to the right here, you can see -


153
00:06:16,950 --> 00:06:18,950
an example of a kanban board with - 

154
00:06:19,150 --> 00:06:21,150
 several tasks and cards.

155
00:06:21,830 --> 00:06:23,490
There are usually 4 cards, 

156
00:06:23,540 --> 00:06:25,660
but here, we also have a 5th card for -

157
00:06:25,750 --> 00:06:28,120
 "URGENT" which denotes a task -

158
00:06:28,160 --> 00:06:30,770
that needs to be completed as soon as possible.

159
00:06:30,970 --> 00:06:32,970
Now going through this, you'll -

160
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:35,000
notice we have a "TODO" section.

161
00:06:35,120 --> 00:06:36,670
These tasks here, such as -

162
00:06:36,780 --> 00:06:39,330
Report Error Analysis, Report Discussion,

163
00:06:39,390 --> 00:06:41,390
these have yet to be started.

164
00:06:41,590 --> 00:06:43,590
"In Progress", we've got -

165
00:06:43,610 --> 00:06:44,800
a couple tasks here;

166
00:06:44,800 --> 00:06:46,370
such as Visualization,

167
00:06:46,370 --> 00:06:47,710
Report Methodology,

168
00:06:47,690 --> 00:06:48,880
Initial Results,

169
00:06:49,080 --> 00:06:51,080
these are tasks that are currently -

170
00:06:51,060 --> 00:06:52,390
being completed.

171
00:06:52,550 --> 00:06:54,550
And "URGENT", these tasks -

172
00:06:54,510 --> 00:06:55,670
must be completed -

173
00:06:55,630 --> 00:06:57,120
as soon as possible.

174
00:06:57,100 --> 00:06:59,100
It usually means there's a deadline or -

175
00:06:59,130 --> 00:07:01,130
other tasks rely on this one -

176
00:07:01,330 --> 00:07:03,010
to be completed.

177
00:07:03,210 --> 00:07:05,210
And finally, we've got "BLOCKED".

178
00:07:05,510 --> 00:07:07,510
These, are a list of tasks -

179
00:07:07,630 --> 00:07:09,630
where you cannot start them -

180
00:07:09,690 --> 00:07:11,690
until another task has finished.

181
00:07:11,890 --> 00:07:13,470
And there we go,

182
00:07:13,490 --> 00:07:15,490
"COMPLETED" on the side, where these -

183
00:07:15,450 --> 00:07:18,350
are just a list of your completed tasks.

184
00:07:20,190 --> 00:07:22,190
In a Kanban board, tasks -

185
00:07:22,140 --> 00:07:25,700
are broken down into four main categories.

186
00:07:25,900 --> 00:07:27,400
Tasks to do,

187
00:07:27,600 --> 00:07:28,990
tasks in progress,

188
00:07:29,180 --> 00:07:30,940
tasks that are blocked,

189
00:07:31,140 --> 00:07:33,140
and tasks that are completed.

190
00:07:33,370 --> 00:07:35,370
Whenever you generate tasks in a standup,


191
00:07:35,570 --> 00:07:37,570
 you add them to "to do".

192
00:07:37,770 --> 00:07:39,770
When you start your task, 

193
00:07:39,969 --> 00:07:41,969
you move that task to "in progress".

194
00:07:42,170 --> 00:07:44,070
And if your task is "blocked" by -

195
00:07:44,060 --> 00:07:44,890
someone else, 

196
00:07:44,920 --> 00:07:46,920
for example, it relies on another -

197
00:07:46,980 --> 00:07:48,980
person to finish their task,

198
00:07:49,180 --> 00:07:51,180
then you move it to "blocked" .

199
00:07:51,270 --> 00:07:53,590
That is, your tasks' progress is

200
00:07:53,790 --> 00:07:57,570
blocked until the prerequisite task is completed.

201
00:07:57,770 --> 00:07:59,770
When you finish your task, you can -

202
00:07:59,810 --> 00:08:01,810
then add it to "completed" .

203
